  "prompt": "A bag contains 5 white, 7 red and 8 black balls. If four balls are drawn one by one without replacement, what is the probability of getting all white balls?",
  "response": "To determine the probability of drawing four white balls consecutively without replacement from a bag containing 5 white, 7 red, and 8 black balls, we will first compute the total number of ways to draw four balls from the total set.\n\nThe total number of balls in the bag is:\n\\[ 5 (\\text{white}) + 7 (\\text{red}) + 8 (\\text{black}) = 20 \\text{ balls} \\]\n\nNow, we compute the total number of ways to choose 4 balls out of these 20:\n\\[ \n\\text{Total number of ways} = \\text{C}(20, 4) = \\frac{20!}{4!(20-4)!} = \\frac{20!}{4! \\cdot 16!}\n\\]\n\nThis results in 4845.\n\\[\n\\text{C}(20, 4) = \\frac{20 \\times 19 \\times 18 \\times 17}{4 \\times 3 \\times 2 \\times 1} = 4845\n\\]\n\nNext, we will compute the number of ways to successfully draw 4 white balls from the 5 available. Specifically, we need to choose all 4 from those 5:\n\\[\n\\text{Number of ways to choose 4 white balls} = \\text{C}(5, 4) = \\frac{5!}{4!(5-4)!} = \\frac{5!}{4! \\cdot 1!} = 5\n\\]\n\nThe probability of drawing 4 white balls (without replacement) is given by the ratio of the successful outcomes to the total outcomes:\n\\[\n\\text{Probability} = \\frac{\\text{Number of successful outcomes}}{\\text{Total number of outcomes}} = \\frac{\\text{C}(5, 4)}{\\text{C}(20, 4)} = \\frac{5}{4845}\n\\]\n\nThus, the exact probability is:\n\\[\n\\frac{5}{4845}\n\\]\n\nThis can be simplified, but is already in its lowest form. For practical purposes, the probability is quite small.",
